<Layout
	title="About One Thousand Works"
	description="Independent publishing house dedicated to books that clarify tomorrow's complex trends."
	pubDate={new Date('July 01 2026')}
	heroImage="/blog-placeholder-about.jpg"
>
	<p>
		<strong>One Thousand Works</strong> is an independent publishing label dedicated to producing books that help people understand and navigate the future. We live in an era of unprecedented acceleration, where macroeconomics, geopolitics, and cutting-edge technologies like Artificial Intelligence intersect in ways that shape our daily lives. Our mission is to bridge the gap between complex analytical insights and accessible, thought-provoking literature.
	</p>

	<h2>Our Editorial Philosophy</h2>
	<p>
		We believe that the best way to understand the future is to look closely at the patterns of the past, combined with a sharp analysis of current technological shifts. Our titles—spanning macroeconomic essays, history, and practical guides to emerging technology—are carefully selected to offer readers survival maps for the economic and technological transitions ahead.
	</p>

	<blockquote>
		"Yesterday is history, tomorrow is a mystery, but understanding their connection is what prepares us for the work ahead."
	</blockquote>

	<h2>What We Publish</h2>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Macroeconomic Perspectives:</strong> Books like <em>Eco dos Loucos Anos 20</em> that trace economic cycles and prepare readers for major market shifts.</li>
		<li><strong>Technology & Work:</strong> Guides like <em>Rendimento Extra com Inteligência Artificial</em> that explore how new tools redefine income, entrepreneurship, and creativity.</li>
		<li><strong>Ideas for Tomorrow:</strong> Non-fiction essays exploring how human behavior—from collective greed to individual adaptability—remains the true anchor of history.</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Why One Thousand Works?</h2>
	<p>
		The name represents the dedication, refinement, and persistent effort that goes into crafting ideas that last. We collaborate with independent authors, economists, and tech pioneers who are not afraid to ask challenging questions. Rather than chasing short-lived headlines, we focus on publishing books that remain relevant years after their release.
	</p>
</Layout>
